=================================================
  jp_draw: Drawing utilities v0.15.1
       James Philbin <philbinj@gmail.com>
       Relja Arandjelovic <relja@robots.ox.ac.uk>
=================================================
A python module used for drawing onto images. Mainly useful for drawing
ellipses as it doesn't seem that any standard library can do this.
The original code was made by James Philbin and was a part of a much larger
project, Relja Arandjelovic isolated the drawing part.


Requirements
============
1. Python
2. Numpy
3. Cython
4. C++ compiler
5. Cairo
6. libjpeg

On Ubuntu:
sudo apt-get install build-essential python python-numpy cython libcairo2-dev libjpeg62


Installation
============
1. Check all requirements.
2. Run 'python setup.py install'.
3. Assuming there are no errors, you're done!
